                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12710408" author="techhusky" created="Mon, 18 May 2009 18:16:53 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed rev 1 under revision 776009.  This rev provides a means for lifecycle-based validation by extending the LifecycleEventManager with a ValidatingLifecycleEventManager.  The validating version uses a pluggable validation implementation to determine if validation should take place and then to validate the entity.  A simple JSR-303 based validation impl wrapper is also included.  The config code to enable validation (use the validating lifecycle event manager and plug in the validation impl) will be added under a separate item.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12761281" author="ppoddar@apache.org" created="Thu, 1 Oct 2009 18:44:32 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Is the following a bug in ValidatingLifeCycleManager and its correction?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@@ -75,7 +74,7 @@&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;return _validator.validating(source, LifecycleEvent.BEFORE_PERSIST) ||&lt;br/&gt;
+        return _validator.validating(source, LifecycleEvent.BEFORE_UPDATE) ||&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;@@ -84,7 +83,7 @@&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;return _validator.validating(source, LifecycleEvent.BEFORE_UPDATE) ||&lt;br/&gt;
+        return _validator.validating(source, LifecycleEvent.BEFORE_PERSIST) ||&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12761282" author="ppoddar@apache.org" created="Thu, 1 Oct 2009 18:46:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;1. ValidatingLifeCycleEventManager : The JavaDoc for constructor is incorrect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. ValidatingLifeCycleEventManager : Carries some auto-generated method headers&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3. Validator interface JavaDoc is incorrect.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
